node.text:
@dr.zelana suggests doing these things every day to improve your emotional well-being: 

1. Start your day with water before all else
2. Step outside for fresh air daily
3. Eat sitting down 
4. Connect with a friend
5. Create a consistent bedtime ritual 

Will you be incorporating these practices into your day? Let me know in the comments.

node.text:
Don't bug out! Cicada season is approaching in many states, so @marascampo and I did a quick Q&A with entomologist, Mike Deutsch ⬇️ 

➡️ How often do cicadas appear? 

➡️ How long are cicadas around for?

➡️ Are cicadas dangerous? 

➡️ Why do cicadas make so much noise!?

➡️ Is there anything I can do to repel cicadas? 

For more on this topic, plus travel + safety tips from @thepointsguy, be sure to watch #TheDrOzShow tomorrow. 
.
.
.
#Summer #Bugs #Cicadas #CicadaSeason #BugsLife

Did you know that when you go to sleep your skin actually goes to work?

Head to the Beauty section on doctoroz.com for more info📱

Made possible by our partner @lorealparis.

node.title: How to Repair Your Skin Overnight

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Dr. Oz on September 18, 2021. May be an image of 1 person, standing, tree and grass.

node.text: I visited my childhood home on the Pennsylvania-Delaware border today. My dad had me mow this lawn weekly, and I almost miss the epic fights over this chore. Always good to remember our roots…

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Dr. Oz on September 18, 2021. May be an image of 2 people, people standing and outdoors.

node.text:
Lots of excitement at the Renaissance Fair. I met this falconer who introduced me to a peregrine falcon—the fastest bird in the world. 

The bird in the video, however, is a vulture. Do you know why it’s important to look alive when a vulture flies near you? These birds eat cadavers (and don’t get sick because their stomachs are so acidic). Who knew?

For more information, visit wildliferevealed.org.
